# Godot 4 project.
#
# Godot's binary/text resource formats (.tscn, .tres, project.godot) are
# plain text and fine to normalize. Image/audio/font assets are NOT text —
# without an explicit `binary` rule here, a Windows client with
# core.autocrlf=true can rewrite lone LF bytes inside them as CRLF on
# checkout, corrupting the file silently (this bit us once: PNGs that were
# byte-correct in the repo failed to load on a Windows checkout with
# "No loader found for resource").
* text=auto eol=lf

*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.webp binary
*.ogg binary
*.wav binary
*.mp3 binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ico binary
